description: The Mandarin turns the crew of a sunken Russian submarine into zombies, pitting them against Iron Man and Force Works.
name: And the Sea Shall Give Up its Dead

description:
For a long time, the mysterious Ultimo has laid dormant and hidden on Earth. However, thanks to the Mandarin, M.O.D.O.K. and Justin Hammer, this powerful robot is revived as a weapon against Stark Enterprises.

It takes some doing and a template device to gain control over Ultimo, but the results are worth it the capture of Iron Man. War Machine leads the fight against Ultimo, while Century tries to locate and rescue Iron Man. Unfortunately, War Machine unknowingly blasts the template off of Ultimo. Now, Ultimo is free to embark on his true purpose leaving everyone with a big problem.
name: Rejoice! I Am Ultimo Thy Deliverer

description:
Militaries are going on full alert, and a financial crisis is ensuing. Even worse, someone is greatly profiting off of all of this. Unsurprisingly, the Mandarin and M.O.D.O.K. are at work by reprogramming Stark Enterprises' own satellites, no less. Also, M.O.D.O.K. brainwashes Jim into turning against Tony.

As a result, Tony is publicly accused and arrested for what has been happening. Bailed out of jail by Julia, Tony has a plan to get to the bottom of this which requires hitching a ride into space with a new satellite. However, will Iron Man battle the brainwashed War Machine to prove his innocence? For that matter, will he even have a choice?
name: Data In, Chaos Out

description: OLIVER MEETS THE CANARY Oliver (Stephen Amell) discovers a man who goes by the name The Mayor (guest star Cle Bennett) is bringing illegal guns in to The Glades, so Oliver sponsors a Cash for Guns event to help clean up the city. Unfortunately, The Mayor crashes the event with his gang and seriously injures Sin (guest star Bex Taylor-Klaus). The Canary (Caity Lotz) is furious when she learns her friend is in the hospital and sets out for revenge. Meanwhile, Felicity (Emily Bett Rickards) stuns Oliver with a bit of information about the Canary, Donner (guest star Dylan Bruce) asks Laurel (Katie Cassidy) to dinner, and Diggle (David Ramsey) reconnects with an old friend.
name: Crucible
What Are Little Girls Made Of?

deck: While on a mapping mission, the USS Enterprise encounters a large spinning cube in outer space.
name: The Corbomite Maneuver

deck: Goku, Pan, and Trunks make it to the top of Imekca's most wanted list.
description: Imecka, Goku, Pan, and Trunks mount a rescue mission to salvage their ship. Without it, theyll be stuck on Imecka forever!

deck: Kirk grants shore leave for the crew on a planet in the Omicron Delta system.
name: Shore Leave

description: Baron Jozek, furious at Batman for humiliating him at a dinner party (over Jozek's underworld connections), hires Josiah Wormwood, a master in setting traps for his victims, to hunt down Batman and bring back the hero's cape and cowl.
name: The Cape and Cowl Conspiracy

deck: A Ninja has been robbing various properties owned by Bruce Wayne. Batman discovers the ninja is his old rival from Japan who has come to Gotham for revenge against Wayne.
description: A mysterious ninja is robbing Wayne Enterprises subsidiaries, and Batman discovers that the ninja is actually his equal in combat. A grudge against Bruce Wayne and skills to match him can only mean one person: Kyodai Ken, an old rival of Wayne's teacher from his days in Japan, and who was thrown out of the dojo after attempting to rob it, only to be stopped by Wayne. Ken, it turns out, wants revenge.
name: Night of the Ninja

description: Catwoman has Batman caught up in a conspiracy involving Professor Milo and Roland Daggett in a diseased animal conspiracy to infect the city with a controlled virus in effort to profit off infected innocents for a pricey cure.
name: Cat Scratch Fever

description: Edward Nygma creates the game The Riddle of the Minotaur and makes millions for the company Competitron. He is then fired by his superior, Daniel Mockridge, who wants the profits for himself. Nygma vows revenge, and two years later, he takes up the mantle of the Riddler and traps Mockridge inside a life-sized version of the Minotaur maze. Batman's sympathy is with Nygma, but he and Robin have to stop him before he kills Mockridge, despite the fact that Mockridge cannot legally be brought to justice. Regardless, Mockridge, despite the resulting rescue, is left in a permanent all-consuming fear of Nygma's return for revenge.
name: If You're So Smart, Why Aren't You Rich?

description: Batman investigates the appearance of a werewolf -like creature in Gotham, not realizing that the monster happens to be one of Bruce Wayne's associates Anthony Romulus , ex-Olympic champion. Behind the scheme is twisted chemist Professor Milo.
name: Moon of the Wolf

description: Kyodai Ken kidnaps Kari, star pupil of Yoru Sensei, the martial arts instructor who taught both Kyodai and Bruce. The ninja's ransom for her is a scroll that teaches the location of the fabled Death Touch.
name: Day of the Samurai

deck: While playing poker Joker, Killer Croc, Penguin, Two-Face, and Poison Ivy recount their times of almost defeating the Batman.
description: The Joker, Killer Croc, the Penguin, Two-Face, and Poison Ivy all meet at a poker table, each telling a tale of times when they almost defeated Batman. At the same time, Harley Quinn is about to kill Catwoman after she rescued Batman from the Joker's electric chair.
name: Almost Got 'Im

description: Bruce Wayne wakes up one morning to find that his life is completely upside-down: his parents are alive, the Batcave does not exist, Alfred does not remember Robin, and he is engaged to Selina Kyle. However, it doesn't mean that Batman isn't still around, and Bruce starts to wonder what has happened, especially after seeing the characteristics of a dream (such as book and newspaper prints not making sense) inside this new life.
name: Perchance to Dream
